Steps to set up remote port forwarding from local server to Google Cloud VM:

Create firewall rule in Google Cloud Console:

VPC network → Firewall
Name: allow-port-5050
Direction: Ingress
Source: 0.0.0.0/0
TCP port: 5050


On Google VM:

sudo nano /etc/ssh/sshd_config
 
 Add: GatewayPorts yes

sudo systemctl restart ssh

From local server, run:

gcloud compute ssh --zone "ZONE NAME" "INSTANCE NAME" --project "PROJECT NAME" -- -R 0.0.0.0:5050:localhost:5050

Access your app via [VM-IP]:5050